"script": "If you fell feet-first into a black hole, you wouldn't be crushed all at once. Instead, gravity would yank your feet far harder than your head, because they're slightly closer to the center. So your body would start to stretch, longer and thinner, like a strand of spaghetti. Scientists actually call this spaghettification. For a small black hole, it would shred you in an instant. But near a giant one, the stretch is gentle at first, so you might cross the point of no return without even feeling it, already doomed and not yet knowing.",
